DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum Immunologic IgM Result
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for immunoglobulin type M (IgM), the major immunoglobulin secreted during a primary immune response, serum immunologic laboratory.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: Serum Immunologic; refers to immunologic features of or immunologic tests done on serum.:The major immunoglobulin secreted during a primary immune response.  IgM binds with low affinity but high avidity (multiple binding sites) because it not only occurs as monomers but also as pentamers and hexamers.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: Pertaining to serologic tests to determine the presence of immunologic factors or evidence of an immune response.

The major immunoglobulin secreted during a primary immune response.  IgM binds with low affinity but high avidity (multiple binding sites) because it not only occurs as monomers but also as pentamers and hexamers.
